The Lake Merritt multi-use path circles the lake and is a popular destination for locals and tourists alike. It is family-friendly, a great place for a dog walk, and is often used by runners and cyclists. 

There is not a designated parking lot for the lake so you will likely have to park on the street.

The Lakeside Park features a bird sanctuary, a boathouse, a great restaurant - Lake Chalet - with fabulous outdoor space, an amphitheater, and a gorgeous botanical garden that includes a bonsai section, and a butterfly garden. At the boathouse, paddleboats can be rented hourly and daily for the whole family. The lake is a great place for picnics and gatherings as there are many shady and sunny spots to relax. 

The park is also home to Fairyland, the first children’s amusement park (after which Disneyland was modeled). Fairyland is $12 for visitors ages 1-100 and is open Friday thru Sunday 10 AM - 4 PM. The majority of the path has restaurants, cafes, and markets nearby and there are toilets located near the Oakland Courthouse. 

