Step back in time as you explore the remnants of the once vast estate of George and Clara Patterson, whose family farmed the land for over 100 years, beginning in the 1850s. Ardenwood Historic Farm is open from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. Tuesdays through Sundays, year-round, including Labor Day and Memorial Day. Ardenwood is closed on Thanksgiving and Christmas Day. For picnic, reservations call 1-888-EBPARKS or 1-888-327-2757, and press option 2. There is no parking fee. Dogs are not allowed in the Ardenwood Historic Farm.

In addition to the bucolic farm scenery, there are farm animals, Patterson mansion tours, and farming demonstrations appealing to both kids and adults. There's also a train ride for the kids. The quirkiest building on the walk not to be missed is the combination windmill-water tank house.

